With events starting up again and seeing the potential usefulness for such a tool, I decided to make this as a proof-of-concept.

github.com

jonathandao0/FrcMatchTimes

Contribute to jonathandao0/FrcMatchTimes development by creating an account on GitHub.

Given an event code and Twitch vods/Youtube videos, it will attempt to generate the appropriate timestamped URL so that you can rewatch the match almost instantly. This uses the public API of TBA, Twitch, and Youtube in order to do so automatically.

Uses:

  • Finding timestamps to split a recorded stream into separate videos for each match
  • Instant reply of matches for streamed events for scouting/strategy

Limitations:

  • Matches that don’t have the actual match start time will use the scheduled time, which will most likely be off.
  • This only works on officially recorded matches, so no replays/practice/test matches will show up

I just made this as a proof-of-concept, so there are probably a few issues with this. Feel free to expand on this idea.
